article.headline: Lipscomb 75, North Florida 67
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- James Poindexter led Lipscomb with 16 points in the team's 75-67 victory of North Florida Monday. North Florida (3-10, 0-6 A-Sun) took a 20-10 lead early in the game, but Lipscomb (8-6, 4-2 A-Sun) then took over, outscoring North Florida 31-8 before halftime. In the second half, North Florida got back in the game with a 14-2 run. Eight of the 14 points came from David Ashwell, who finished with 15 points. After North Florida had cut its 41-28 halftime deficit to a single point (43-42), Lipscomb's Brian Fisk, who totaled 13 points for the game, scored five points in a 7-2 run. Besides Poindexter and Fisk, three other Lipscomb players scored in the double digits. Eddie Ard scored 14 points, Michael Lusk scored 13 and Shaun Durant scored 10. North Florida's Rashad Williams also scored 15 points to tie for the team high, and Ryan Daugherty added 13 points. North Florida shot 49 percent from the floor and out-rebounded Lipscomb, 32-31. Lipscomb shot 47 percent and scored 25 points off 15 North Florida turnovers.
